    <chapter line="1">17-18. Peyyālavaggādivaṇṇanā</chapter>
    <paragraph line="2" number="164-184"><bold>Samanuñño</bold>ti <pageBreak edition="V" number="2.0240" /> samānajjhāsayo. <bold>Rāgassā</bold>ti pañcakāmaguṇikarāgassa. <bold>Abhiññāyā</bold>ti abhijānanatthaṃ. <bold>Suññato samādhī</bold>tiādīhi tīhipi samādhīhi vipassanāva kathitā. Vipassanā hi niccābhinivesa-niccanimitta-niccapaṇidhiādīnaṃ abhāvā imāni nāmāni labhati. <bold>Pariññāyā</bold>ti parijānanatthaṃ. Sesapadesupi eseva nayoti.</paragraph>
    <centered line="3">Peyyālavaggādi niṭṭhitā.</centered>
    <centered line="4">Manorathapūraṇiyā aṅguttaranikāya-aṭṭhakathāya</centered>
    <centered line="5">Tikanipātassa saṃvaṇṇanā niṭṭhitā.</centered>
    <centered line="6"> Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa</centered>
    <nikaya line="7">Aṅguttaranikāye</nikaya>
    <book line="8">Catukkanipāta-aṭṭhakathā</book>
    <title line="9">1. Paṭhamapaṇṇāsakaṃ</title>
